1
00:00:13,300 --> 00:00:14,780
(International Hotel)

2
00:00:17,376 --> 00:00:19,550
Chief, we don't have enough
witnesses or evidence yet.

3
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:20,550
Are we arresting him now?

4
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:21,710
Shouldn't we wait for Young Master Zhao?

5
00:00:21,710 --> 00:00:22,710
He might have a clue.

6
00:00:22,710 --> 00:00:23,480
There's no time.

7
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:24,480
Pans is a British citizen.

8
00:00:24,490 --> 00:00:26,490
Once he reaches Shanghai,
he's out of our lands.

9
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:27,760
Then we won't arrest him.

10
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:28,280
Yes, sir.

11
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:35,500
=Cases Between Us=

12
00:00:35,980 --> 00:00:38,860
=Episode 21=

13
00:00:41,790 --> 00:00:44,150
Father Pans, please come with us
to the police department

14
00:00:44,150 --> 00:00:44,920
for questioning.

15
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:46,240
Why?

16
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:48,110
We suspect you
of animal abuse and arson.

17
00:00:48,390 --> 00:00:49,640
Do you have any evidence?

18
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:52,600
Your police have a habit
of accusing people without proof.

19
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:54,070
Now you're targeting

20
00:00:54,070 --> 00:00:55,350
a British citizen?

21
00:00:56,670 --> 00:00:58,070
Where did you reporters come from?

22
00:00:58,070 --> 00:00:58,880
Chief Yuan,

23
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:01,280
what evidence do you have
that proves Father Pans is guilty?

24
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:04,272
Do you have a warrant for his arrest?
Did you get the proper authorization?

25
00:01:04,590 --> 00:01:05,790
Which newspaper are you with?

26
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:07,350
Police business. Stop taking pictures.

27
00:01:07,350 --> 00:01:08,310
You abused animals.

28
00:01:08,920 --> 00:01:10,560
When your adopted son,
Dong Zhi, found out

29
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:11,350
you started the fire

30
00:01:11,350 --> 00:01:12,280
to silence him.

31
00:01:13,510 --> 00:01:15,310
Your adopted daughter,
Wen's disappearance,

32
00:01:15,310 --> 00:01:16,510
is also tied to you.

33
00:01:16,510 --> 00:01:17,150
And

34
00:01:17,510 --> 00:01:19,870
you bribed the Li family's housekeeper,
Zhang Hualan,

35
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:22,760
to drug Li Siqiao,
who witnessed your crimes.

36
00:01:26,510 --> 00:01:27,840
How imaginative of you.

37
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,480
You ought to write novels
for the newspaper.

38
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,950
This isn't imagination.

39
00:01:32,430 --> 00:01:33,920
We brought Director Li's dog

40
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:34,560
to your house.

41
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:35,430
It was terrified.

42
00:01:35,710 --> 00:01:36,310
Why?

43
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:38,640
Because it had been
locked up there before

44
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:40,120
for animal experiments.

45
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:40,710
We found

46
00:01:40,710 --> 00:01:42,000
three more dogs like it.

47
00:01:42,096 --> 00:01:43,870
Their bodies were covered
with needle marks

48
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:45,310
and ligature marks.

49
00:01:45,310 --> 00:01:46,272
Take a look at his hands.

50
00:01:46,336 --> 00:01:48,350
See the callus
between his thumb and index finger.

51
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:50,400
That's from frequent use
of metal scissors

52
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,950
and scalpels.

53
00:01:52,272 --> 00:01:53,560
You're a doctor, aren't you?

54
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:55,070
I am.

55
00:01:55,070 --> 00:01:57,070
That doesn't mean I abuse animals.

56
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:58,310
Besides,

57
00:01:58,310 --> 00:02:00,280
what's wrong with killing a few dogs?

58
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:03,840
Which law says I can't?

59
00:02:04,230 --> 00:02:07,310
Using stray dogs for medical experiments

60
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:09,190
isn't illegal in China.

61
00:02:09,744 --> 00:02:11,568
The fire at your house
wasn't an accident.

62
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:14,470
You deliberately set it with kerosene.

63
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,710
If you insist on accusing me,

64
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,360
there's no point in defending myself.

65
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:20,190
I'm a priest

66
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,520
and a British citizen.

67
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:22,590
Do you think

68
00:02:22,590 --> 00:02:24,870
these baseless accusations

69
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:26,840
will convict me in court?

70
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,430
Then may I search

71
00:02:28,430 --> 00:02:29,910
your church and residence?

72
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,150
By all means.

73
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:35,710
Since Chief Yuan
is so certain I'm guilty,

74
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:39,560
why not give it a thorough search?

75
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:42,910
Come with me.

76
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,630
Search the whole place.

77
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,800
Thoroughly.

78
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,280
Leave no corner unchecked.

79
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,224
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

80
00:03:33,310 --> 00:03:33,960
Sir,

81
00:03:34,150 --> 00:03:35,360
nothing suspicious was found.

82
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,000
What?

83
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:38,960
No evidence?

84
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:42,240
Chief Yuan,
you do enjoy making up stories.

85
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:43,840
In that case,

86
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:46,120
allow me to tell you mine.

87
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:48,750
Two years ago,

88
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:51,630
I adopted the mute girl,
Wen, in Tianjin.

89
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:54,560
Half a year ago,
before coming to Beijing,

90
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,400
I adopted Dong Zhi.

91
00:03:59,150 --> 00:03:59,840
Dong Zhi,

92
00:04:00,150 --> 00:04:01,280
have some more meat.

93
00:04:01,630 --> 00:04:03,310
(Dong Zhi)
(I treated the boy better,)

94
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:05,030
(and Wen got jealous.)

95
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:07,430
(Wen)
(She became unstable.)

96
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:09,870
That day we argued.

97
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:13,000
She stabbed my leg
with a pair of scissors,

98
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,430
and then ran away.

99
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:16,830
If you don't believe me,

100
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:18,920
you may examine the wound.

101
00:04:19,630 --> 00:04:20,870
After it was bandaged,

102
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,240
I lay down to rest.

103
00:04:22,950 --> 00:04:25,120
Dong Zhi was reading in my room.

104
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:26,680
Who would've thought

105
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:30,720
that Wen poured kerosene
through the house, set it on fire,

106
00:04:31,870 --> 00:04:33,390
and locked the door from the outside?

107
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,240
Dong Zhi!

108
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,070
Dong Zhi!

109
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,870
Wake up, Dong Zhi!

110
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:43,040
Dong Zhi!

111
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:43,870
Wake up!

112
00:04:59,430 --> 00:05:01,000
You're saying a ten-year-old girl

113
00:05:01,270 --> 00:05:03,240
started that fire all by herself,

114
00:05:04,310 --> 00:05:05,600
and you never noticed a thing?

115
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:08,720
Satan disguises himself
as an angel of light.

116
00:05:09,270 --> 00:05:11,510
I simply failed
to see through his disguise.

117
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:17,800
Are you satisfied

118
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:18,830
with this explanation?

119
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,160
It seems

120
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:23,160
I've now proven

121
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,310
my innocence.

122
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:27,160
In that case,

123
00:05:27,510 --> 00:05:29,040
the reporters' photos

124
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:31,240
will be in tomorrow's papers.

125
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:34,190
Chief Yuan, prepare to face
disciplinary action.

126
00:05:34,430 --> 00:05:37,920
You'll pay for your recklessness.

127
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,720
Father Pans,

128
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,830
one moment.

129
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,070
Allow me to introduce myself.

130
00:05:56,070 --> 00:05:57,824
I'm Zhao Shaoshang,
Investigative Consultant

131
00:05:57,888 --> 00:05:59,630
of Division Four,
Jingshi Police Department.

132
00:05:59,950 --> 00:06:02,032
Chief Yuan was overeager
to solve the case.

133
00:06:02,064 --> 00:06:03,950
That's how
this misunderstanding happened.

134
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:05,040
I'm sure a gentleman like you

135
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:06,120
won't stoop

136
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:07,120
to our level.

137
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:09,510
Your Chinese police

138
00:06:09,510 --> 00:06:12,310
have shown no respect
for citizens of the British Empire.

139
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,830
Do you think a worthless apology

140
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:17,190
is enough to settle this?

141
00:06:17,952 --> 00:06:20,390
I'm only a small fry. My apology
doesn't carry much weight.

142
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:20,920
This is

143
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:21,510
Director Li.

144
00:06:21,510 --> 00:06:23,720
He's the highest-ranking officer
in the department.

145
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:25,248
His apology should be worthy enough.

146
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,560
Pans.

147
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,720
Mr. Pans, right?

148
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,950
A pleasure.

149
00:06:28,950 --> 00:06:30,240
I'm terribly sorry.

150
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,720
The standards in our department,

151
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,720
well,

152
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:33,920
you've seen them.

153
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,070
Please be understanding.

154
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,120
I hear

155
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:40,310
you're quite the collector.

156
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,680
A pair of Qianlong enamel vases

157
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:44,560
just came out of Prince Gong's estate
the other day.

158
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:47,070
Perhaps you'd be willing to show us
a little leniency?

159
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:00,390
Very well.

160
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:03,190
The Bishop teaches us to forgive.

161
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:04,680
If so,

162
00:07:05,430 --> 00:07:07,190
I'll let this pass.

163
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:09,040
But...

164
00:07:09,750 --> 00:07:11,040
if there's a next time,

165
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:13,160
the disgraceful conduct
of the Chinese police

166
00:07:13,328 --> 00:07:15,560
will be splashed across
newspapers around the world.

167
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:19,160
Take care.

168
00:07:25,648 --> 00:07:28,160
Let's go. We don't fight a battle
we're not prepared to win.

169
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:38,390
Explain.

170
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:39,430
What was that?

171
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:43,750
This afternoon,

172
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,510
I had Zhao Cai check

173
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,560
every kerosene shop

174
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,750
near Wen's home.

175
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:55,190
Sir,

176
00:07:55,630 --> 00:07:57,560
has this little girl
bought kerosene here?

177
00:07:58,750 --> 00:07:59,480
Yes,

178
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:00,240
she has.

179
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,560
I remember

180
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:03,240
she bought five one-jin cans.

181
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,120
I asked her,

182
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,360
"Why did your parents send you

183
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,040
to buy kerosene all by yourself?"

184
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:08,720
Right.

185
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,660
Could Pans have sent her

186
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:12,360
to buy kerosene?

187
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:14,390
I considered that, too.

188
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,360
But judging from the scene,

189
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:17,920
everything Pans said checks out.

190
00:08:18,750 --> 00:08:20,560
(The kerosene on the floor formed a ring)

191
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,870
(around Pan's bed.)

192
00:08:22,896 --> 00:08:24,240
(It means whoever started the fire)

193
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,270
(was after him.)

194
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,000
(And the marks on the latch
of the side room)

195
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:29,920
(show it was locked from the outside,)

196
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,720
(then scraped open from the inside
with a knife.)

197
00:08:32,910 --> 00:08:34,870
You think Wen did it?

198
00:08:35,670 --> 00:08:36,200
No.

199
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:38,670
She couldn't have bribed Ms. Zhang

200
00:08:38,670 --> 00:08:39,790
to drug Li Siqiao.

201
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,030
Pan's story

202
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:43,080
only sounds convincing.

203
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:47,790
Didn't we agree

204
00:08:47,790 --> 00:08:48,630
to split up

205
00:08:48,630 --> 00:08:50,320
and regroup after we found some leads?

206
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,208
If he'd made it to Shanghai,

207
00:08:52,210 --> 00:08:54,150
we couldn't have arrested him,
even with evidence.

208
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,550
It was the only option.

209
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:03,600
You're usually level-headed.

210
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,960
Why did you lose your temper

211
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:05,510
when you dealt

212
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:06,440
with Westerners?

213
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:07,630
What?

214
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:09,120
Did you get bullied in Britain?

215
00:09:09,670 --> 00:09:10,360
No.

216
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,670
I never lost a fight.

217
00:09:12,670 --> 00:09:14,630
I got top marks in every subject.

218
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:15,960
But my teachers

219
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,630
never believed

220
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:20,080
a Chinese student
could outperform white students.

221
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,390
I can't stand that kind of insult.

222
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,480
These scoundrels.

223
00:09:26,030 --> 00:09:27,390
All the more reason

224
00:09:27,390 --> 00:09:29,440
you have to keep your head
when dealing with them.

225
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:29,960
Before,

226
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,550
I heard the British had acquired

227
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:32,832
a batch of Chinese treasures.

228
00:09:32,864 --> 00:09:34,120
I wanted to get them back.

229
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,270
Guess what they said?

230
00:09:35,270 --> 00:09:36,750
They said it wasn't about the money.

231
00:09:36,928 --> 00:09:37,952
Then what was it about?

232
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:39,000
The law.

233
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,120
They've had it all figured out.

234
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,030
Even the artifacts taken from tombs

235
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,670
came with official seals

236
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,720
and perfectly legal paperwork.

237
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:47,870
That's when I realized

238
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:49,056
you have to be extra careful

239
00:09:49,056 --> 00:09:50,150
with Westerners.

240
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,432
You're not actually planning
to give him

241
00:09:54,464 --> 00:09:55,630
that antique vase, are you?

242
00:09:55,630 --> 00:09:56,600
Fat chance.

243
00:09:57,184 --> 00:09:58,320
I'll give him a fake.

244
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,480
That'd be doing a good deed.

245
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,510
What does he even know?

246
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:05,960
Hello?

247
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:08,910
Alright.

248
00:10:09,390 --> 00:10:10,080
Keep looking.

249
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:12,790
What is it?

250
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:13,790
They found it.

251
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:17,200
Dong Zhi was buried at Anhe Cemetery.

252
00:10:18,016 --> 00:10:19,510
We'll have to exhume the body, right?

253
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,270
Don't worry.

254
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,080
Pans may have something

255
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,510
on you,

256
00:10:24,550 --> 00:10:25,270
but I've got

257
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,240
a few tricks of my own.

258
00:10:39,460 --> 00:10:41,540
(Anhe Cemetery)

259
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:50,000
In the antiques trade,
you'll find all kinds of people.

260
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,240
As long as you have money,

261
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,080
it's not hard to find tomb raiders.

262
00:10:54,750 --> 00:10:57,150
So you were lying to me

263
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:58,750
when you said you don't deal

264
00:10:58,750 --> 00:10:59,600
with tomb raiders?

265
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,240
What?

266
00:11:01,376 --> 00:11:02,790
Are you going to run me in?

267
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,630
Or to cover for me?

268
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:12,240
I'd cuff you first.

269
00:11:12,870 --> 00:11:13,550
Young Master.

270
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:14,550
Young Master.

271
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,200
The grave diggers sent word.

272
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:16,910
You were right.

273
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:24,700
(Dong Zhi)

274
00:11:25,630 --> 00:11:26,080
Hurry.

275
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:32,790
What is this?

276
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:40,200
(Morgue)
It's the middle of the night.

277
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,720
Can't this wait till morning?

278
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,960
We don't have a warrant.

279
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:44,630
Why do you always do this?

280
00:11:44,992 --> 00:11:45,888
Just do the autopsy.

281
00:11:45,904 --> 00:11:48,030
Find something suspicious,
and we'll have our paperwork.

282
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:48,910
Fine, fine.

283
00:11:48,910 --> 00:11:49,550
Wait here.

284
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,510
Where are you going?

285
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:13,030
Report.

286
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:14,390
Can't you read?

287
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:16,000
Your money's still with me.

288
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:28,670
The victim was struck in the face
with a blunt object.

289
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:31,480
The nasal bones, cheekbones,
and eye sockets were all shattered.

290
00:12:31,616 --> 00:12:32,720
There was soot in his lungs.

291
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,240
This confirms he was burned alive.

292
00:12:35,328 --> 00:12:36,864
He wasn't dumped there after death.

293
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:38,720
Go on.

294
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:39,750
That's it.

295
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:41,240
That's it?

296
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:42,200
That's all.

297
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:45,870
That's not enough
to charge Father Pans.

298
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,200
What if his face had been injured

299
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,000
before the fire?

300
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:51,550
Pans said

301
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,480
that the cabinet fell
on him from the front.

302
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,000
If that's true,

303
00:12:55,056 --> 00:12:57,360
he may have used the fresh injuries
to cover up the old ones.

304
00:12:58,270 --> 00:12:59,320
Everything's charred.

305
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,928
How can we tell old injuries from new?

306
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:03,030
If your theory is right,

307
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:05,200
then the mummy Li Siqiao saw

308
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:06,790
was Dong Zhi.

309
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,960
To silence Li Siqiao,

310
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:11,910
Pans had to buy off Ms. Zhang.

311
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,550
We need to find her.

312
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:16,080
She's probably already dead.

313
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,240
When I confronted Pans,

314
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:19,360
he didn't panic at all.

315
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:20,670
Then find Wen.

316
00:13:21,270 --> 00:13:22,960
If Pan is the killer,

317
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,830
there's a good chance
Wen witnessed everything.

318
00:13:24,910 --> 00:13:25,960
But what if

319
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:27,150
she's been silenced, too?

320
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,960
I had Zhao Cai ask around

321
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,390
the Sanlihe neighborhood.

322
00:13:30,390 --> 00:13:31,270
Every neighbor said

323
00:13:31,270 --> 00:13:32,320
Pans told them

324
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:34,150
he'd be leaving the day after tomorrow.

325
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,200
I think

326
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,480
he wanted that news

327
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:37,510
to reach Wen,

328
00:13:37,510 --> 00:13:38,670
so she'd come looking for him.

329
00:13:38,910 --> 00:13:39,960
Why would she?

330
00:13:41,670 --> 00:13:42,510
To kill him.

331
00:13:42,704 --> 00:13:44,688
Pans is confident he can kill her first.

332
00:14:14,782 --> 00:14:17,302
(Zhang)

333
00:14:48,630 --> 00:14:49,910
Cigarettes for sale!

334
00:14:50,790 --> 00:14:52,080
Cigarettes for sale!

335
00:14:53,870 --> 00:14:55,000
Want a pack, sir?

336
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:00,000
Cigarettes for sale!

337
00:15:26,270 --> 00:15:28,840
Murder!

338
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:51,320
I was wondering where to find you.

339
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:53,790
And here you are.

340
00:15:54,390 --> 00:15:56,080
Since you and your brother
were so close,

341
00:15:56,550 --> 00:15:58,030
you can join him.

342
00:16:57,510 --> 00:16:58,910
I'm a British citizen.

343
00:16:59,150 --> 00:17:00,000
I'm also a priest...

344
00:17:01,670 --> 00:17:03,030
Suspect Pans,

345
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:05,750
you attempted murder
with a firearm in public.

346
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:06,960
Take him back for questioning.

347
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:10,070
What are you doing?

348
00:17:15,020 --> 00:17:19,020
(Jingshi Police Department)

349
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:32,640
She says thank you.

350
00:17:38,790 --> 00:17:39,920
I'll explain the case.

351
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:43,110
Just nod or shake your head.

352
00:17:47,888 --> 00:17:48,720
The fire at your home

353
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:50,590
on Renshou Alley...

354
00:17:50,590 --> 00:17:51,440
Did you start it?

355
00:17:57,110 --> 00:17:58,350
Who did?

356
00:18:07,110 --> 00:18:09,920
Did you lock the side room
where Pans was staying?

357
00:18:17,310 --> 00:18:18,270
Did you know

358
00:18:18,270 --> 00:18:20,480
both he and your brother were inside?

359
00:18:31,260 --> 00:18:33,580
(End of Episode 21)

360
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:36,800
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

361
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,340
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

362
00:18:38,340 --> 00:18:39,590
♪However, the world changes♪

363
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:41,510
♪You'll still be by my side♪

364
00:18:41,510 --> 00:18:43,200
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

365
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,770
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

366
00:18:44,770 --> 00:18:46,340
♪If this is my final chapter♪

367
00:18:46,340 --> 00:18:48,840
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
